February 13, 2003<br>
Period 4<br>
<br>
<br>
Influential Characters<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I believe that the two characters who influence Huck the most in the book are his father, Pap, and the two con men, the Duke and King, because talks very seriously of the changes that they have caused in him. Pap is an awful mean drunkard of a father to Huck and only comes home to him when it will profit him in some way. Pap drinks incessantly and is violent and highly irrational when intoxicated chasing Huck around inside their shanty saying he is going to kill Huck. Huck reflects Pap’s influence not only in his crude manner but also in Huck’s reaction to drunkenness at a circus he visits by showing great concern for a performer pretending to be drunk. The King and Duke also greatly influence Huck in that they turn Huck away from lying because they con people out of what is theirs with their very hurtful lies. I believe that Huck sees what he might become in the future with the King and the Duke and is repulsed by their awful and unscrupulous characters. In the book Huck states that he thinks what they do is horrible and really shows their significant influence upon him.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I believe that the most significant event which changes Huck is when Huck sees Buck mowed down in a hail of gunfire. This event in the book amounts to a loss of innocence in Huck which all children eventually go through. While Huck has weathered a very tough childhood without a mother and a drunkard father he has probably never seen anything like someone he knows and cares about getting brutally shot to death. When Huck drags Buck’s corpse on to shore and cover’s it over he sits and cries over Buck realizing he is gone forever. I think that this single event in the book influenced Huck the most in the book.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00CC00><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmrcliffordsenglishclasses.showUserPublicProfile?gid=winston1@mrcliffordsenglishclasses>winston1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#00CC00>(2/13/03 11:00:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmrcliffordsenglishclassesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Response to Chelsea</span><hr size=1> Churchill's response <br>
