I agree with Chelsea in that Jim influenced Huck greatly throughout the novel because he really made Huck think that slaves were like white people (but not great enough to make him an abolitionist). Though Jim’s character is not very well developed or respected in the novel he still manages to influence Huck greatly.<br>
The point I disagree with Chelsea on is her argument that Tom is more influential than Pap or Duke and King in influencing Huck in the novel. While Tom does serve as an influence to widen Huck’s education Huck only thinks of him as a fun friend and not as someone who really influenced him.<br>
